column5: Those poor Lac Seul Walleye are in for one bad week when the boys arrive next week. Those Walleye better feed heavy now because next week when they decide to have a snack it will be one of the boys jigs. Hope you are lucky enough to be one of the boys.
You guys are wannabees. I've seen your presentations and I'm not fooled. I weigh in at 14 plus lbs and have my weigh around the bay......try try again...hehehe

The eyes have no need to fear, I'm not one of the afore-mentioned "boys". As that wiley old 14 pounder knows, I am his master! He could only respond to this post because I practice CPR on all but a few eaters. --- BD aka "The Walleye Master" ;)
Those Walleye are in a lot of trouble next week. Hope we leave some of those Lac Seul beautys for you fellas coming up later this summer.
So many silly notes. The bottom line is on Lac Suel anyone, including my 4 year old can catch decent fish.
Your 4 year old son is lucky.
Mayflies are about to hatch. Will make things tough all over. My money is on the four year old.
